RoR setup.

StackSkills RoR dev course.

Ubuntu 18.04 VM ruby
Desktop install

http://railsapps.github.io/installrubyonrails-ubuntu.html for install

## env set up
source /etc/profile.d/rvm.sh

gem -v # version of ruby
gem list #list gems installed
gem outdated #list of outdated gems
gem update #update outdated gems


## env maintenance
gem install bundler #bundler is the gem management platform
gem install nokogiri #major dependency, keep this one up to date

## rails installation
gem install rails # installs stable version of ails

saundo@ruby:~$ rails -v
Rails 5.2.1


## git project instantiation
CREATE GIT REPO
copy in ssh key, then
eval $(ssh-agent)
ssh-add / private key
git config --global user.name "Chris Saunderson"
git config --global user.email "23367976+csaunderson@users.noreply.github.com"
## this allows the remote push to github without exposing email address to world

mkdir projects/rails
cd projects/rails
git init
vi README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin git@github.com:csaunderson/rails.git
git push -u origin master

